File & Directory Manipulation 
cd: Navigating through complex directory structures (e.g., cd ../subdir).
mkdir -p: Creating nested directories for multi-stage simulations (e.g., mkdir -p project/run1/dos).
cp / mv: Copying or renaming input files (cp file1 file2).
rm: Deleting files, rm *.out to clear output files.
ln -s: Linking large pseudopotential files to current directories, avoiding duplication.
